forbidden.name: no-circular
forbidden.comment: This dependency is part of a circular relationship. You might want to revise your solution (i.e. use dependency inversion, make sure the modules have a single responsibility)

forbidden.name: no-orphans
forbidden.comment: This is an orphan module - it's likely not used (anymore?). Either use it or remove it. If it's logical this module is an orphan (i.e. it's a config file), add an exception for it in your dependency-cruiser configuration. By default this rule does not scrutinize dot-files (e.g. .eslintrc.js), TypeScript declaration files (.d.ts), tsconfig.json and some of the babel and webpack configs.
